              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value based on the input parameters provided. This function is designed to generate or retrieve a unique sequence identifier for an account, which is used to ensure that each account has a distinct identifier within a database system."
        }
